			    STPJS 306</div>
  <p class="cont">tabernacles, then died and again have risen and received glorified bodies, they will have an
  ascendency over the spirits who have received no bodies, or kept not their first estate,<span class="footRef">1</span> like the devil.
  The punishment of the devil was that he should not have a habitation like men.<span class="footRef">2</span> The devil&rsquo;s
  retaliation is, he comes into this world, binds up men&rsquo;s bodies, and occupies them himself.<span class="footRef">3</span> When
  the authorities come along, they eject him from a stolen habitation.<span class="footRef">4</span></p>
  <p class="std">The design of the great God in sending us into this world,<span class="footRef">5</span> and organizing us to prepare us for
  the eternal worlds, I shall keep in my own bosom at present.</p>
  <p class="std">We have no claim in our eternal compact, in relation to eternal things, unless our actions and
  contracts<span class="footRef">6</span> and all things tend to this. But after all this, you have got to make your calling and election
  sure.<span class="footRef">7</span> If this injunction would lie largely on those to whom it was spoken, how much more those of
  the present generation!</p>
  <p class="std">1st key: Knowledge<span class="footRef">8</span> is the power of salvation.<span class="footRef">9</span> 2nd key: Make your calling and election sure.<span class="footRef">10</span>
  3rd key: It is one thing to be on the mount and hear the excellent voice,<span class="footRef">11</span> etc., and another to hear
  the voice declare to you, You have a part and lot in that kingdom.<span class="footRef">12</span> (May 21, 1843.) DHC
  5:401–403.</p>
  <div class="topic">The Prophet on Forming Temperance Societies</div>
  <p class="std">Dear Brother:&mdash;In answer to yours of May 4th, concerning the Latter-day Saints forming a
  temperance society, we would say, as Paul said&mdash;&ldquo;Be not unequally yoked with unbelievers,<span class="footRef">13</span> but
  contend for the faith once delivered to the Saints&rdquo;;<span class="footRef">14</span> and as Peter advises, so say we,</p>
  <p class="std">&ldquo;Add to your knowledge, temperance.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">15</span> As Paul said he had to become all things to all men,
  that he might thereby save some,<span class="footRef">16</span> so must the elders of the last days do; and, being sent out to
  preach the Gospel<span class="footRef">17</span> and warn the world of the judgments<span class="footRef">18</span> to come, we are sure, when they teach
  as directed by the Spirit,<span class="footRef">19</span> according to the revelations<span class="footRef">20</span> of Jesus Christ,<span class="footRef">21</span> that they will preach the
  truth<span class="footRef">22</span> and prosper without complaint. Thus we have no new commandment to give, but admonish
  elders and members<span class="footRef">23</span> to live by every word that proceedeth forth from the mouth of God,<span class="footRef">24</span> lest they
  come short of the glory<span class="footRef">25</span> that is reserved for the faithful.<span class="footRef">26</span> (May 22, 1843.) DHC 5:404.</p>
